sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as Client
    participant LLS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant Inline as GarakInlineEvalAdapter
    participant Remote as GarakRemoteEvalAdapter
    participant Garak as Garak Subprocess
    participant KFP as KFP API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KFPPod as KFP Pipeline Pods
    participant vLLM as vLLM Inference<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Files as Llama Stack Files API<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Safety as Llama Stack Safety API<br/>8321/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,Files: Flow 1: Inline Garak Scan (Llama Stack)
        Client->>LLS: POST /alpha/eval/run-eval<br/>Bearer Token
        LLS->>Inline: Route to provider (in-process)
        Inline->>Inline: Resolve config cascade<br/>(predefined + user overrides)
        Inline->>Garak: Launch subprocess<br/>(os.setsid, SIGTERM/SIGKILL)
        Garak->>vLLM: Inference requests<br/>HTTPS, API key
        vLLM-->>Garak: Model responses
        Garak-->>Inline: Scan results (JSONL)
        Inline->>Inline: Parse results, compute TBSA score
        Inline->>Files: Upload report artifacts<br/>Bearer Token
        Inline-->>LLS: Job ID + status
        LLS-->>Client: Job ID
        Client->>LLS: GET /alpha/eval/jobs/status
        LLS-->>Client: Status (running/completed)
        Client->>LLS: GET /alpha/eval/jobs/retrieve
        LLS-->>Client: Scores + metrics
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Remote KFP Scan (Llama Stack)
        Client->>LLS: POST /alpha/eval/run-eval<br/>Bearer Token
        LLS->>Remote: Route to provider (in-process)
        Remote->>Remote: Build KFP pipeline<br/>(resolve container image)
        Remote->>KFP: Submit pipeline run<br/>HTTPS, Bearer Token
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 1: validate
        KFPPod->>LLS: Validate config<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 2: resolve_taxonomy
        KFPPod->>Files: Download taxonomy<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 3: sdg_generate
        KFPPod->>KFPPod: Generate adversarial prompts<br/>via sdg-hub
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 4: prepare_prompts
        KFPPod->>Files: Upload prompts<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 5: garak_scan
        KFPPod->>vLLM: Vulnerability scan<br/>HTTPS, API key
        KFPPod->>Files: Upload results<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 6: parse_results
        KFPPod->>Files: Upload reports<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        Remote->>KFP: Poll status<br/>HTTPS, Bearer Token
        Remote->>Files: Retrieve results<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        Remote-->>LLS: Scores + metrics
        LLS-->>Client: Results
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Eval-Hub KFP Scan
        Note right of Client: Eval-Hub Controller creates K8s Job
        Client->>Inline: GarakAdapter.run()<br/>Eval-Hub SDK
        Inline->>KFP: Submit S3-based pipeline<br/>HTTPS, Bearer Token
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 1-2: validate + taxonomy
        KFPPod->>S3: Read/write artifacts<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 3-4: SDG + prompts
        KFPPod->>S3: Store prompts<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 5: garak_scan
        KFPPod->>vLLM: Vulnerability scan<br/>HTTPS, API key
        KFPPod->>S3: Store results<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM
        KFP->>KFPPod: Step 6: write_kfp_outputs
        KFPPod->>S3: Final artifacts<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM
        Inline->>S3: Download results<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM
        Inline->>Inline: Parse + generate HTML report
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 255)
        Note over Client,Safety: Flow 4: Shield Scan (Guardrail Testing)
        Client->>LLS: Run shield scan
        LLS->>Inline: Shield scan request
        Inline->>Safety: Run input shield<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        Safety-->>Inline: Shield result (pass/block)
        Inline->>vLLM: Forward to model<br/>HTTPS, API key
        vLLM-->>Inline: Model response
        Inline->>Safety: Run output shield<br/>HTTP, Bearer Token
        Safety-->>Inline: Shield result (pass/block)
        Inline-->>LLS: Combined results
    end
